<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbfca4bce-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s13619"><num value="13619">§ 13619.</num><heading> “Covered section 8 housing” defined</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For purposes of this subchapter, the term “covered section 8 housing” means housing described in <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s13641/2/G">section 13641(2)(G) of this title</ref> that was originally designed for occupancy by elderly families.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbfca4bcf-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/102/550/tVI/s659">Pub. L. 102–550, title VI, § 659</ref>, <date date="1992-10-28">Oct. 28, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/3825">106 Stat. 3825</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
